							</header><!-- .entry-header -->

							
							<div class="entry-content">
								
<p class="has-drop-cap">If Giorgetto Giugiaro had made it into art school, the Volkswagen Golf might never have been created, James Bond might never have had a submersible Lotus Esprit, Marty McFly might never have travelled through time in a DeLorean and Hyundai might never have made cars.</p>



<p>But Giugiaro failed to make art school and so, reluctantly, went into car design instead. He&#8217;s now, aged 84, arguably the greatest living car designer with a host of truly memorable, groundbreaking and beloved vehicles to his name.</p>



<p>He is still designing and creating cars, and recently helped create a running version of his classic 1974 Hyundai Pony Coup√© concept, powered by an 80bhp 1.2-litre four-cylinder petrol engine, almost 50 years after it was unveiled at the Turin Motor Show.</p>



<p>But painting is his true joy and passion as the video I filmed with him shows, and the interview below explores in more detail. </p>



<p>Oddly, asked which artist Giugiaro would like to have collaborated with to make a car, he did not say one of the Renaissance masters such as Da Vinci or Michelangelo; instead he picked Dutch post-impressionist Vincent Van Gogh. That gives an insight into the style of this master of car design.</p>



<hr class="wp-block-separator has-alpha-channel-opacity is-style-dots"/>



<p><strong>Jeremy Hart: What was your reaction when you were approached to rebuild the Pony Coup√©, since the 1974 original no longer exists?</strong></p>



<p>Giorgetto Giugiaro: It is interesting and also a bit strange to recreate a design from about 50 years ago. Fortunately, I still have some drawings. However, certainly the spirit is different: I am a different age, there is no longer the enthusiasm of youth, my point of view has changed. </p>



<p>Also, technologies have changed; at that time there were very few of them. Doing by hand today what was done back then is more difficult, because all that craftsmanship of those who made the models (e.g., the beaters) has disappeared. Today it is more difficult to do the ‚Äúold‚Äù things, while it is easier to do the overall work thanks to all the computer apparatus. </p>



<p>So, this request surprised me but I‚Äôm also happy at the idea of still being able to do such work again.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" width="3791" height="1800" src="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-3.jpg?w=1024" alt="Hyundai Pony Coupe Concept side view" class="wp-image-132090" srcset="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-3.jpg 3791w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-3.jpg?resize=310,147 310w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-3.jpg?resize=768,365 768w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-3.jpg?resize=1024,486 1024w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-3.jpg?resize=1536,729 1536w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-3.jpg?resize=2048,972 2048w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-3.jpg?resize=620,294 620w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-3.jpg?resize=360,171 360w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-3.jpg?resize=720,342 720w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-3.jpg?resize=400,190 400w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-3.jpg?resize=800,380 800w" sizes="(max-width: 3791px) 100vw, 3791px" /></figure>



<p><strong>JH: Do you remember how the phone call went that started the project?</strong></p>



<p>GG: I was in my office with Fabrizio. Of course, I was surprised and a bit displaced. The idea of going to the archive searching for drawings, original photos to reconstruct something that is no longer there immediately won us over.</p>



<p><strong>JH: In general, is there a car that has particularly excited you in so many years of work?</strong></p>



<p>GG: Certainly. The 1955 Citro√´n DS 19. At that time I was a student, and it was the car that made me finally decide to get involved in car design. It struck me in a special way because it was completely different from all the other cars. To me it is still today a unique car in architecture; it is inimitable.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-pullquote"><blockquote><p>&#8216;The 1970s was a time when the engineering side had to give way to the vision of designers&#8217;</p></blockquote></figure>



<p><strong>JH: From Lotus to Alfa Sud, you have created so many cars. Where do you place the Hyundai Pony Coup√© in this landscape?</strong></p>



<p>GG: Let&#8217;s say first of all that the Pony Coup√© was born out of research work to show, starting from a widely used car like the sedan (saloon) version, how it was possible to create a product that was more hedonistic and not simply tied to Korea&#8217;s needs of the moment. </p>



<p>This coup√© gave shape to a vision; the one of a country that with the sedan was beginning to have an original mass-produced and popular product, and that for this reason could also begin to think of other, sportier, more fun products. </p>



<p>I believe it is a project that tells the story of the transformation of a country with a great desire to produce, which ‚Äî after the necessary ‚Äî also began to look at pleasure.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="3840" height="1920" src="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-4.jpg?w=1024" alt="Hyundai Pony Coupe Concept overhead view" class="wp-image-132091" srcset="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-4.jpg 3840w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-4.jpg?resize=310,155 310w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-4.jpg?resize=768,384 768w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-4.jpg?resize=1024,512 1024w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-4.jpg?resize=1536,768 1536w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-4.jpg?resize=2048,1024 2048w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-4.jpg?resize=620,310 620w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-4.jpg?resize=360,180 360w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-4.jpg?resize=720,360 720w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-4.jpg?resize=400,200 400w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-4.jpg?resize=800,400 800w" sizes="(max-width: 3840px) 100vw, 3840px" /></figure>



<p><strong>JH: If you had to rank them, what place would Pony Coup√© occupy in your works?</strong></p>



<p>Being in a non-performance niche, the Coup√© was aimed at those who wanted something sporty, brilliant in the aesthetics but on a &#8220;normal&#8221;, non-performance car. I would not rank it; I see it as a project that looks at sports cars without being a sports car. It is the form of an idea, an attitude.</p>



<p><strong>JH: When Hyundai called you in &#8217;74 to build the Pony, you had to start from scratch ‚Äî it was all a blank sheet of paper. What was it like to work with nothing behind you? Where did you find the inspiration?</strong></p>



<p>GG: Working on a project means first of all understanding the context in which you operate. In this case, it was a country that wanted to enter such an important sector as the automobile industry with a car of its own design and which started from a base, from an already existing chassis (Mitsubishi&#8217;s). </p>



<p>There was a series of industrial constraints to be taken into account: what could be done with what was available in terms of suppliers in a context in which there was no automobile industry with its own established supply chain. So the project was determined by these starting conditions. </p>



<p>When this project was presented, there was also a certain amount of surprise because it was not as advanced as others I had overseen, but obviously it was not possible to make a comparison: the European automotive industry had a history and means at its disposal that could not be those of a fledgling industry. </p>



<p>Pony responded to a need for ease, it had to be comfortable in terms of interior space and trunk space, but it had to be an easy car to assemble because it didn&#8217;t have an established organisation behind it.</p>



<p>It was not an easy project to realise but it was very consistent with the needs and the context in which it was to fit.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-2 is-cropped wp-block-gallery-1 is-layout-flex wp-block-gallery-is-layout-flex">
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="3084" height="2057" data-id="132092" src="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-6.jpg?w=1024" alt="Hyundai Pony Coupe Concept launch" class="wp-image-132092" srcset="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-6.jpg 3084w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-6.jpg?resize=310,207 310w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-6.jpg?resize=768,512 768w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-6.jpg?resize=1024,683 1024w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-6.jpg?resize=1536,1024 1536w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-6.jpg?resize=2048,1366 2048w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-6.jpg?resize=579,386 579w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-6.jpg?resize=336,224 336w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-6.jpg?resize=672,448 672w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-6.jpg?resize=373,249 373w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/1974-Pony-Coupe-Concept-6.jpg?resize=747,498 747w" sizes="(max-width: 3084px) 100vw, 3084px" /></figure>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" width="7771" height="5181" data-id="132094" src="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/Large-54957-InauguralHyundaiReunionCelebratesRebirthofHyundaiMotorsPonyCoupeConcept.jpg?w=1024" alt="Giorgetto Giugiaro at the Hyundai Pony Coupe Concept launch" class="wp-image-132094" srcset="https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/Large-54957-InauguralHyundaiReunionCelebratesRebirthofHyundaiMotorsPonyCoupeConcept.jpg 7771w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/Large-54957-InauguralHyundaiReunionCelebratesRebirthofHyundaiMotorsPonyCoupeConcept.jpg?resize=310,207 310w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/Large-54957-InauguralHyundaiReunionCelebratesRebirthofHyundaiMotorsPonyCoupeConcept.jpg?resize=768,512 768w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/Large-54957-InauguralHyundaiReunionCelebratesRebirthofHyundaiMotorsPonyCoupeConcept.jpg?resize=1024,683 1024w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/Large-54957-InauguralHyundaiReunionCelebratesRebirthofHyundaiMotorsPonyCoupeConcept.jpg?resize=1536,1024 1536w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/Large-54957-InauguralHyundaiReunionCelebratesRebirthofHyundaiMotorsPonyCoupeConcept.jpg?resize=2048,1365 2048w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/Large-54957-InauguralHyundaiReunionCelebratesRebirthofHyundaiMotorsPonyCoupeConcept.jpg?resize=579,386 579w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/Large-54957-InauguralHyundaiReunionCelebratesRebirthofHyundaiMotorsPonyCoupeConcept.jpg?resize=336,224 336w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/Large-54957-InauguralHyundaiReunionCelebratesRebirthofHyundaiMotorsPonyCoupeConcept.jpg?resize=672,448 672w, https://www.driving.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/sites/5/2023/08/Large-54957-InauguralHyundaiReunionCelebratesRe